David BURNET, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, v. BROWN-CRUMMER COMPANY. No. 825. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. March 10, 1933. C. M. Charest, General Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Elcock & Martin, of Wichita, Kan., for respondent.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
